79,-0.020660903,-0.019161107,0.006169285,0.07044878,-0.026722955,-0.010997213,0.013034149,-0.048785225,-0.032970764,0.024161572,0.011331915,-0.016586758,0.029957045,0.006674959,0.015453028,-0.03234256,-0.011567825,0.021227159,0.006607622,-0.014538429,-0.03881573,-0.040298406,-0.040936507,-0.012431171,-0.005229488,-0.034035813,-0.038363,-0.011489146,0.028250016,-0.000701555,-0.03408436,0.049366973,-0.013181734,-0.005046981,0.019855984,0.038657803,0.017707441,-0.004756701,-0.000530879,0.02526622,0.005090912,0.025697367,0.01289299,-0.026170058,0.003899605,0.001571772,-0.014913491,-0.030879177,0.0352574,-0.019807974,-0.046101805,0.018200064,0.008522145,0.019172346,0.06976227,0.009541031,-0.009900589,0.02752698,-0.029397216,-0.000833523,-0.029002655,-0.032178745,-0.007192319,0.020117037,0.020058334,-0.035291348,0.00884822,-0.050215088]'::vector, '2026-03-14T19:51:52.380Z');
INSERT INTO knowledge_patterns (id, clause_pattern, category, contract_type, risk_level, why_risky, safer_alternative, jurisdiction_notes, embedding, created_at) VALUES ('a1b2c3d4-6002-4a00-8000-000000000029', 'Landlord shall have no duty of care with respect to the safety or security of Tenant, Tenant''s family members, guests, or invitees, whether on the Premises or in common areas, and assumes no responsibility for any criminal acts of third parties.', 'liability_waiver', '["lease"]'::jsonb, 'yellow', 'While landlords are not guarantors of tenant safety against all crime, they do have a duty to maintain common areas safely and to take reasonable security measures, especially if they are aware of safety problems. If the landlord knows the building''s front door lock has been broken for months and a break-in occurs, they should bear some responsibility. This clause attempts to eliminate that duty entirely, including responsibility for hazards the landlord could easily fix.', 'Landlord shall take reasonable measures to maintain the safety and security of common areas, including functioning locks on all exterior doors, adequate lighting in hallways and parking areas, and prompt repair of security features. While Landlord does not guarantee the safety of Tenant against criminal acts of third parties, Landlord shall not be relieved of liability for injuries resulting from Landlord''s failure to maintain the Premises in a reasonably safe and secure condition.', 'Kline v. 1500 Massachusetts Ave. Apartment Corp., 439 F.2d 477 (D.C. Cir. 1970) established landlord''s duty to take reasonable security measures in common areas. California Civil Code Section 1714 establishes a general duty of care. UK Occupiers'' Liability Act 1957 imposes a duty of care on occupiers (including landlords) toward visitors. Defective Premises Act 1972 Section 4 imposes a duty of care regarding maintenance.', '[-0.022028284,0.05240893,-0.006939193,0.003675165,-0.025456449,-0.09106559,-0.08094613,