26,0.04463178,0.09875743,-0.03769902,-0.042927913,0.004386432,-0.017137095,0.010065212,-0.028461741,0.002881689,-0.059951972,0.001739201,-0.028496267,-0.035066012,-0.022377849,0.012908706,-0.001939303,0.007046465,-0.014678809,-0.025424015,-0.039906863,-0.010015218,0.018221172,-0.024049286,0.00880702,-0.030226946,0.02759359,0.03982904,-0.010839256,0.032785058,-0.003825445,-0.003783697,-0.025177067,-0.007645155,0.06281709,-0.009515815,-0.007826802,0.039373696,-0.049456343,0.006341542,-0.005569947,0.044908397,-0.035517283,-0.028251683,-0.039156083,0.018412026,-0.00672806,-0.006902615,0.026770094,-0.060101554,0.004563684,-0.05028228,-0.026008327,0.034080733,-0.009379832,-0.027024604]'::vector, '2026-03-14T19:51:56.569Z');
INSERT INTO knowledge_patterns (id, clause_pattern, category, contract_type, risk_level, why_risky, safer_alternative, jurisdiction_notes, embedding, created_at) VALUES ('c3e3f4a5-b6c7-4d8e-9f0a-2b3c4d5e6f7a', 'The Receiving Party agrees that during the term of this Agreement and for a period of three (3) years thereafter, it shall not directly or indirectly engage in any business that competes with the Disclosing Party''s business in any geographic market in which the Disclosing Party operates or plans to operate.', 'non_solicitation', '["nda"]'::jsonb, 'red', 'This is a full non-compete agreement buried inside an NDA. It bans you from competing with the other party for three years in any market they operate in — or even plan to operate in (which could be anywhere). This has nothing to do with protecting confidential information and everything to do with eliminating competition. Non-competes are banned or heavily restricted in many US states and are generally unenforceable when hidden in an NDA because they go far beyond what''s needed to protect trade secrets.', 'For the avoidance of doubt, nothing in this Agreement shall restrict either party from independently developing products or services that may compete with the other party''s products or services, provided that the Receiving Party does not use the Disclosing Party''s Confidential Information in connection with such development.', 'US: California (Bus. & Prof. Code Section 16600), Oklahoma, North Dakota, and Minnesota ban most non-competes. FTC''s 2024 non-compete rule (currently in litigation) would broadly restrict non-competes. Restatement (Second) of Contracts Section 188 — restraints must be reasonable and ancillary to a legitimate transaction. EU: Non-competes within NDAs must satisfy proportionality under national employment laws. UK: Restraint of trade doctrine — non-competes must protect a legitimate interest, be reasonable in scope and duration, and be in the public interest.', '[0.020164121,-0.02