36,0.01642197,0.039897766,-0.03766552,0.015835261,-0.051120456,-0.012951003,0.005218806,-0.043676168,-0.03863339,0.009782643,-0.020343972,0.000413182,-0.03221729,-0.043621596,-0.044875186,-0.010610138,0.051287934,-0.053103793,0.018255163,-0.032953776,-0.007226145,0.055247165,-0.013039167,0.053344913,-0.017450154,-0.019011846,-0.013754401,-0.02422355,0.049838305,-0.026288344,-0.006365955,0.028239185,-0.07244713,0.013906786,-0.005632443,0.012665835,-0.014847386,-0.053114817,-0.03965047,0.006338255,-0.049735017,-0.036290906,0.016403995,-0.083716735,0.000733385,-0.038683835,-0.006050493,0.046605535,0.002355707,0.013143902]'::vector, '2026-03-14T19:51:56.569Z');
INSERT INTO knowledge_patterns (id, clause_pattern, category, contract_type, risk_level, why_risky, safer_alternative, jurisdiction_notes, embedding, created_at) VALUES ('b2010203-0405-4607-8809-0a0b0c0d0e0f', 'Payment for Services rendered shall be due within ninety (90) days following Client''s receipt and approval of a correct and undisputed invoice. Client reserves the right to dispute any invoice within the 90-day period, in which case payment shall be suspended until the dispute is resolved to Client''s satisfaction.', 'payment_terms', '["freelance"]'::jsonb, 'red', 'Net-90 means you wait three months to get paid, and the client can delay indefinitely by ''disputing'' the invoice on any grounds. The phrase ''resolved to Client''s satisfaction'' gives them total control -- there''s no objective standard for what counts as resolved. You could complete work perfectly and still never get paid.', 'Payment for Services rendered shall be due within thirty (30) days following Contractor''s submission of a correct invoice. Client may dispute specific line items in writing within fourteen (14) days of receipt, but shall pay all undisputed amounts by the original due date. Disputed amounts shall be resolved within thirty (30) days through good-faith negotiation.', 'The UK Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998 sets a default payment term of 30 days and allows the creditor to charge statutory interest (8% + Bank of England base rate) on late payments. EU Late Payment Directive 2011/7/EU Article 3(5) provides that payment periods exceeding 60 days shall not be grossly unfair. The Freelancers Union reports that 71% of freelancers have trouble getting paid; net-90 with subjective dispute rights exacerbates this.', '[-0.028917551,0.007348217,-0.033884678,-0.05753095,-0.076004334,-0.034624048,-0.023086369,0.011396585,0.017178288,-0.031707183,-0.005188919,0.0030646,-0.04500699,-0.025675785,0.053120084,-0.005465121,-0.084313974,0.01989409,0.00313725,0.03461621,0.01