9,-0.0417667,0.004095462,0.006465921,0.023236746,-0.001616534,0.048614454,-0.086155765,0.055550184,0.019834934,-0.014102768,0.022821216,-0.041851047,-0.005346791,-0.027293256,0.036178775,0.019155063,-0.017113687,-0.002276871,0.04546035,-0.003415172,-0.001015752,-0.009812057,0.018509481,0.013820931,-0.08236657,0.024248093,-0.031804048,0.016503735,0.006685508,-0.018840428,0.010955215,0.009000742,-0.017707855,-0.035832286,0.002049392,-0.08737414,-0.045268685,0.0279004,-0.035524853,-0.021500237,-0.011369521,-0.04104415]'::vector, '2026-03-14T19:51:52.380Z');
INSERT INTO knowledge_patterns (id, clause_pattern, category, contract_type, risk_level, why_risky, safer_alternative, jurisdiction_notes, embedding, created_at) VALUES ('a1b2c3d4-7002-4a00-a000-000000000033', 'Landlord reserves the right to relocate Tenant to a comparable unit within the building or an affiliated property at any time during the lease term, at Landlord''s sole discretion, and Tenant agrees to cooperate with any such relocation within 14 days of notice.', 'quiet_enjoyment', '["lease"]'::jsonb, 'red', 'You signed a lease for a specific apartment, not a random unit the landlord chooses. Forced relocation disrupts your life, may change your commute, neighborhood, or school district, and ''comparable'' is subjective -- the landlord decides what counts as comparable. This is effectively an eviction disguised as a relocation, and it strips away the certainty that a lease is supposed to provide. Fourteen days is insufficient time to organize a move.', 'Tenant shall not be required to relocate to a different unit during the lease term. If relocation becomes necessary due to emergency repairs or safety concerns, Landlord shall (a) obtain Tenant''s written consent, (b) provide a unit of equal or greater size and quality at the same rent, (c) pay all moving costs, and (d) provide at least 30 days'' notice. Tenant may alternatively terminate the Lease without penalty.', 'Most US jurisdictions recognize that a lease creates a property interest in a specific unit; unilateral relocation violates this interest. California Civil Code Section 789.3 prohibits landlord actions intended to influence a tenant to vacate. UK Protection from Eviction Act 1977 Section 1 makes it an offence to unlawfully deprive a residential occupier of their occupation. EU Directive 93/13/EEC Annex paragraph (f) targets unilateral contract modification rights.', '[-0.025766684,0.041621804,-0.010863664,-0.045939628,-0.023218947,-0.018552626,-0.028716138,0.042195696,0.03651662,-0.023884878,0.0