67,0.013120958,-0.014145179,-0.006368419,0.003915295,0.002441218,0.001441942,0.03074106,-0.00263793,-0.06055408,-0.002517042,0.02480462,0.0323035,-0.03242041,-0.006750561,0.030656567,-0.026931059,0.024498513,-0.03125795,-0.002655642,0.01932398,0.005679567,0.003559149,0.009234386,0.002819377,-0.031317066,-0.008246758,-0.019524794,-0.01068554,-0.058980882,0.017891109,-0.001195578,-0.02999952,0.000248283]'::vector, '2026-03-14T19:51:52.380Z');
INSERT INTO knowledge_patterns (id, clause_pattern, category, contract_type, risk_level, why_risky, safer_alternative, jurisdiction_notes, embedding, created_at) VALUES ('a1b2c3d4-8002-4a00-b000-000000000036', 'If Landlord grants consent to subletting, Tenant shall pay Landlord a non-refundable subletting fee equal to one month''s rent plus 50% of any excess rent collected from the subtenant above Tenant''s current monthly rent.', 'subletting', '["lease"]'::jsonb, 'yellow', 'A full month''s rent as a subletting fee is excessive -- processing a sublet does not cost the landlord a month''s rent. Taking 50% of any ''profit'' from the sublet is even more unusual and acts as a financial disincentive against subletting. In some jurisdictions, landlords can charge a reasonable fee to cover actual administrative costs, but a month''s rent plus a profit share goes well beyond that. This effectively makes subletting economically unviable.', 'If Landlord consents to subletting, Landlord may charge a reasonable administrative fee not to exceed $150 to cover the cost of processing the subletting application, including background and credit checks of the proposed subtenant. No additional fees, profit-sharing, or rent premiums shall be charged in connection with the sublet.', 'New York Real Property Law Section 226-b limits subletting fees to the landlord''s reasonable actual costs. San Francisco Administrative Code Section 6.15 limits sublet fees. UK Tenant Fees Act 2019 prohibits fees for consent to assign or sublet exceeding reasonable costs. EU Directive 93/13/EEC Annex paragraph (e) targets disproportionate compensation requirements.', '[-0.047799237,0.046644308,-0.006594847,-0.03475318,-0.004816423,-0.027542941,-0.025127262,-0.02423207,0.025380356,-0.0264784,0.011065628,-0.031209573,0.000934452,-0.034399875,0.04864477,-0.002812801,-0.014127199,-0.010484052,0.023827814,0.008086535,0.00484309,-0.02623769,0.016105486,0.04750824,-0.012494441,-0.013568607,-0.017877871,-0.03752654